\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs46 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}30 large fresh mint leaves, coarsely torn by hand\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 to 4 thick slices fresh watermelon\
{\listtext	\'95	}12 ounces light rum, such as Bacardi\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup simple syrup\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 tablespoons freshly squeezed lime juice (3 limes)\
{\listtext	\'95	}Sprigs of mint and spears of watermelon, for serving\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs46 \cf0 Use a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mortar-and-pestle/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mortar and pestle}} to mash the mint leaves. Remove and discard the rind and seeds of the watermelon. Put the fruit into a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/food-processor/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 food processor}} fitted with the steel blade and puree. Put the mashed mint into a large pitcher with 2 cups of pureed watermelon, the rum, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simple-syrup/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simple syrup}}, and lime juice and stir to combine. Pour the mixture into a pitcher for serving.\
Place ice cubes in 6 glasses and pour the mojito mixture into the glasses. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garnish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Garnish}} with sprigs of fresh mint and spears of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/watermelon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 watermelon}}. Serve ice cold.}